{
  "stem": "22840.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Same way the Jewish-- Jewish children were taught [INAUDIBLE] I was-- I-- I recited [NON-ENGLISH] every evening from-- from the time I recollect being alive, not knowing what it means.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So they taught me the Otche Nash.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It's interesting that the word was so blurred to each other, that although I spoke perfect-- not perfect, I mean seven-year-old child Slovak, I didn't understand all the words.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "But that was the prayer, Funnily enough, for a Jew, not understanding your prayer was very-- very obvious.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "I didn't understand the Jewish prayer I was praying.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "I knew how to read them, but I didn't understand the words, not all of them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Part of them, but not all of them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I recollect only care and love and worry and support.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They fed me before they ate.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I-- I didn't feel that I were forced on them, and if I was, it may have been the beginning, not toward the end.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I'll tell you, when we come to the proper time, why.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There, where I met the first Germans.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And there is where I-- where I learned how to distinguish between the types of Germans, between the Wehrmacht and the SS-- in our case, the Waffen-SS-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] between the occasional Gestapo, between the patrols patrolling in between the garrison type of people.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was not a garrison resident in Buly but there were people who came, stayed for a couple of hours, sat and had coffee, and I played with their weapon.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That where I became interested in weaponry.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was this old German soldier-- old.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't know how old he was.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
